2 TITL Will of Demsey Taylor
1 _OID 98d39610-d449-47c8-b6b5-dd805fb29adc
1 _DSCR copy provided by Wendy Sykes Lowery
2 CONT North Carolina State Archives Box C.R.071.801.42  Folder: Dempsey Taylor 1851
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>North Carolina State Archives Box C.R.071.801.42&amp;nbsp; Folder: Dempsey Taylor 1851&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;D Taylor Will Sep 1847 &lt;br&gt;To Sep Ses 1851&lt;br&gt;Recorded page 99&lt;br&gt;Jno Odom CCC&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&g
2 CONC t;North Carolina Taylor Wills&lt;br&gt;State of North Carolina N_ampton County&lt;br&gt;In the name of God amen---&lt;br&gt;I Dempsey Taylor being in bad health but of sound mind and memory, thanks be to God for the same, do make and ordain this m
2 CONC y last will and Testament (revoking all others heretofore made) in manner of form following (viz)&lt;br&gt;Item 1st I give to my son Norplet H. Taylor on Bed &amp;amp; furniture&lt;br&gt;Item 2nd I give to my son Richard Taylor the sum of Thirty fi
2 CONC ve Dollars to make up the deficiency in a Horse which I previously gave him and his Heirs forever&lt;br&gt;Item 3rd I give and bequeath to my daughter Ann E.L. Taylor one Bed and furniture also one Trunk now in her possession I also give her a negr
2 CONC o girl Louisa&lt;br&gt;Item 4th I give and bequeath to Norphlet H. Taylor one negro boy Charles-&lt;br&gt;Item 5th I loan to my wife Mary Taylor all of my negroes and all of my Lands and every other species of property of which I may die possesse
2 CONC d after my just debts are paid (be it understood) during her natural life, and at her death I give all my Lands to Norphlet H. Taylor to him and his Heirs forever&amp;mdash;&lt;br&gt;Item 6th It my will and desire that after the decease of my wif
2 CONC e that all my negroes and other property not heretofore disposed of be sold and the money arising from such sale be equally divided between all my children (with the exception) that the children of Jane Maigan (?) and Mary Inman shall receive a pro
2 CONC portionable part of their mothers share as they become twenty one years of age to them &amp;amp; their Heirs forever.&lt;br&gt;Item 7th I hereby constitute and appoint my son Turner P. Taylor Executor of this my last will and Testament ent.- In wit
2 CONC ness whereof I here unto set my hand and affixed my seal this twenty ninth day of September one thousand eight hundred &amp;amp; forty seven. Teste&lt;br&gt;Dempsey Taylor&lt;br&gt;W.S. Copeland, Henry H. Long, Jonathan T Gay&lt;br&gt;Northampton C
2 CONC ounty, September Court 1851 The foregoing last will and Testament of Dempsey Taylor dec was exhibited in open Court and duly proved by the Oath of W.S. Copeland and Jonathan T. Gay, Two of the subscribing witnesses thereto, and by Arthur T. Long wh
2 CONC o ____ the handwriting of Henry H. Long dec. The ___ subscribing witnesses, and the said will was ordered to be certified and recorded. And thereupon William Taylor and Turner H. Taylor two of the Exors named were duly qualified as such.&lt;br&gt;T
2 CONC este John B. Odom C.C.C.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
